\title{Semgrep}

\taxon{skill}

\meta{description}{>-}

\subtree{
\title{Semgrep Security Scan}
\p{Run a Semgrep scan with automatic language detection, parallel execution via Task subagents, and merged SARIF output.}

\subtree{
\title{Essential Principles}
\ol{
\li{\strong{Always use \code{\startverb --metrics=off\stopverb}} — Semgrep sends telemetry by default; \code{\startverb --config auto\stopverb} also phones home. Every \code{\startverb semgrep\stopverb} command must include \code{\startverb --metrics=off\stopverb} to prevent data leakage during security audits.}
\li{\strong{User must approve the scan plan (Step 3 is a hard gate)} — The original "scan this codebase" request is NOT approval. Present exact rulesets, target, engine, and mode; wait for explicit "yes"/"proceed" before spawning scanners.}
\li{\strong{Third-party rulesets are required, not optional} — Trail of Bits, 0xdea, and Decurity rules catch vulnerabilities absent from the official registry. Include them whenever the detected language matches.}
\li{\strong{Spawn all scan Tasks in a single message} — Parallel execution is the core performance advantage. Never spawn Tasks sequentially; always emit all Task tool calls in one response.}
\li{\strong{Always check for Semgrep Pro before scanning} — Pro enables cross-file taint tracking and catches ~250\% more true positives. Skipping the check means silently missing critical inter-file vulnerabilities.}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{When to Use}
\ul{
\li{Security audit of a codebase}
\li{Finding vulnerabilities before code review}
\li{Scanning for known bug patterns}
\li{First-pass static analysis}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{When NOT to Use}
\ul{
\li{Binary analysis → Use binary analysis tools}
\li{Already have Semgrep CI configured → Use existing pipeline}
\li{Need cross-file analysis but no Pro license → Consider CodeQL as alternative}
\li{Creating custom Semgrep rules → Use \code{\startverb semgrep-rule-creator\stopverb} skill}
\li{Porting existing rules to other languages → Use \code{\startverb semgrep-rule-variant-creator\stopverb} skill}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Output Directory}
\p{All scan results, SARIF files, and temporary data are stored in a single output directory.}

\ul{
\li{\strong{If the user specifies an output directory} in their prompt, use it as \code{\startverb OUTPUT_DIR\stopverb}.}
\li{\strong{If not specified}, default to \code{\startverb ./static_analysis_semgrep_1\stopverb}. If that already exists, increment to \code{\startverb _2\stopverb}, \code{\startverb _3\stopverb}, etc.}
}

\p{In both cases, \strong{always create the directory} with \code{\startverb mkdir -p\stopverb} before writing any files.}

\pre{\startverb
# Resolve output directory
if [ -n "$USER_SPECIFIED_DIR" ]; then
  OUTPUT_DIR="$USER_SPECIFIED_DIR"
else
  BASE="static_analysis_semgrep"
  N=1
  while [ -e "${BASE}_${N}" ]; do
    N=$((N + 1))
  done
  OUTPUT_DIR="${BASE}_${N}"
fi
mkdir -p "$OUTPUT_DIR/raw" "$OUTPUT_DIR/results"
\stopverb}

\p{The output directory is resolved \strong{once} at the start of Step 1 and used throughout all subsequent steps.}

\pre{\startverb
$OUTPUT_DIR/
├── rulesets.txt                 # Approved rulesets (logged after Step 3)
├── raw/                         # Per-scan raw output (unfiltered)
│   ├── python-python.json
│   ├── python-python.sarif
│   ├── python-django.json
│   ├── python-django.sarif
│   └── ...
└── results/                     # Final merged output
    └── results.sarif
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Prerequisites}
\p{\strong{Required:} Semgrep CLI (\code{\startverb semgrep --version\stopverb}). If not installed, see [Semgrep installation docs](https://semgrep.dev/docs/getting-started/).}

\p{\strong{Optional:} Semgrep Pro — enables cross-file taint tracking, inter-procedural analysis, and additional languages (Apex, C#, Elixir). Check with:}

\pre{\startverb
semgrep --pro --validate --config p/default 2>/dev/null && echo "Pro available" || echo "OSS only"
\stopverb}

\p{\strong{Limitations:} OSS mode cannot track data flow across files. Pro mode uses \code{\startverb -j 1\stopverb} for cross-file analysis (slower per ruleset, but parallel rulesets compensate).}
}

\subtree{
\title{Scan Modes}
\p{Select mode in Step 2 of the workflow. Mode affects both scanner flags and post-processing.}

\pre{\startverb
| Mode | Coverage | Findings Reported |
|------|----------|-------------------|
| **Run all** | All rulesets, all severity levels | Everything |
| **Important only** | All rulesets, pre- and post-filtered | Security vulns only, medium-high confidence/impact |
\stopverb}

\p{\strong{Important only} applies two filter layers:}

\ol{
\li{\strong{Pre-filter}: \code{\startverb --severity MEDIUM --severity HIGH --severity CRITICAL\stopverb} (CLI flag)}
\li{\strong{Post-filter}: JSON metadata — keeps only \code{\startverb category=security\stopverb}, \code{\startverb confidence∈{MEDIUM,HIGH}\stopverb}, \code{\startverb impact∈{MEDIUM,HIGH}\stopverb}}
}

\p{See [scan-modes.md](references/scan-modes.md) for metadata criteria and jq filter commands.}
}

\subtree{
\title{Orchestration Architecture}
\pre{\startverb
┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│ MAIN AGENT (this skill)                                          │
│ Step 1: Detect languages + check Pro availability                │
│ Step 2: Select scan mode + rulesets (ref: rulesets.md)           │
│ Step 3: Present plan + rulesets, get approval [⛔ HARD GATE]     │
│ Step 4: Spawn parallel scan Tasks (approved rulesets + mode)     │
│ Step 5: Merge results and report                                 │
└──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
         │ Step 4
         ▼
┌─────────────────┐
│ Scan Tasks      │
│ (parallel)      │
├─────────────────┤
│ Python scanner  │
│ JS/TS scanner   │
│ Go scanner      │
│ Docker scanner  │
└─────────────────┘
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Workflow}
\p{\strong{Follow the detailed workflow in [scan-workflow.md](workflows/scan-workflow.md).} Summary:}

\pre{\startverb
| Step | Action | Gate | Key Reference |
|------|--------|------|---------------|
| 1 | Resolve output dir, detect languages + Pro availability | — | Use Glob, not Bash |
| 2 | Select scan mode + rulesets | — | [rulesets.md](references/rulesets.md) |
| 3 | Present plan, get explicit approval | ⛔ HARD | AskUserQuestion |
| 4 | Spawn parallel scan Tasks | — | [scanner-task-prompt.md](references/scanner-task-prompt.md) |
| 5 | Merge results and report | — | Merge script (below) |
\stopverb}

\p{\strong{Task enforcement:} On invocation, create 5 tasks with blockedBy dependencies (each step blocks the previous). Step 3 is a HARD GATE — mark complete ONLY after user explicitly approves.}

\p{\strong{Merge command (Step 5):}}

\pre{\startverb
uv run {baseDir}/scripts/merge_sarif.py $OUTPUT_DIR/raw $OUTPUT_DIR/results/results.sarif
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Agents}
\pre{\startverb
| Agent | Tools | Purpose |
|-------|-------|---------|
| `static-analysis:semgrep-scanner` | Bash | Executes parallel semgrep scans for a language category |
\stopverb}

\p{Use \code{\startverb subagent_type: static-analysis:semgrep-scanner\stopverb} in Step 4 when spawning Task subagents.}
}

\subtree{
\title{Rationalizations to Reject}
\pre{\startverb
| Shortcut | Why It's Wrong |
|----------|----------------|
| "User asked for scan, that's approval" | Original request ≠ plan approval. Present plan, use AskUserQuestion, await explicit "yes" |
| "Step 3 task is blocking, just mark complete" | Lying about task status defeats enforcement. Only mark complete after real approval |
| "I already know what they want" | Assumptions cause scanning wrong directories/rulesets. Present plan for verification |
| "Just use default rulesets" | User must see and approve exact rulesets before scan |
| "Add extra rulesets without asking" | Modifying approved list without consent breaks trust |
| "Third-party rulesets are optional" | Trail of Bits, 0xdea, Decurity catch vulnerabilities not in official registry — REQUIRED |
| "Use --config auto" | Sends metrics; less control over rulesets |
| "One Task at a time" | Defeats parallelism; spawn all Tasks together |
| "Pro is too slow, skip --pro" | Cross-file analysis catches 250% more true positives; worth the time |
| "Semgrep handles GitHub URLs natively" | URL handling fails on repos with non-standard YAML; always clone first |
| "Cleanup is optional" | Cloned repos pollute the user's workspace and accumulate across runs |
| "Use `.` or relative path as target" | Subagents need absolute paths to avoid ambiguity |
| "Let the user pick an output dir later" | Output directory must be resolved at Step 1, before any files are created |
\stopverb}
}

